1. Build Debian 13 image
   a. Run debian13.sh
   b. Wait for the image, debian13.img

2. (Optional) Make a bootable USB drive
   a. Run usb-boot.sh
   b. Wait for the image, usb-boot.img
   c. Flash usb-boot.img to a USB drive
      - dd if=usb-boot.img of=/dev/sdb bs=4M status=progress
   d. Resize the data partition
      - parted /dev/sdb
        > print (Choose 'Fix' if prompted) 
        > resizepart 3 100%
        > print (check the size!)
        > quit
      - mkfs.exfat -L data /dev/sdb3
   e. Mount /dev/sdb3 to /media/usb
   e. Copy debian13.img to /media/usb
   f. Copy android.tar.gz to /media/usb
   h. umount /media/usb

3. Prepare SBC
   a. Boot SBC with the bootable USB
   b. Mount the data partition: mount /dev/sdb3 /media
      - mount /dev/sdb3 /media
   c. cd /media
   d. Flash debian13.img to SBC drive
      - dd if=debian13.img of=/dev/sda bs=4M status=progress
   f. Resize the data partition
      - parted /dev/sda
        > print (Choose 'Fix' if prompted)
        > resizepart 3 100%
        > print (to check the size)
        > quit
      - e2fsck -f /dev/sda3
      - resize2fs /dev/sda3
   g. Unmount and remove USB
   h. Reboot with the disk drive (/dev/sda)

4. Install Android emulator
   a. Download Android SDK (android.tgz) from:
      https://lsg-thermofisher.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/MONARCH/pages/98075180/Builds
   b. Untar android.tgz to /data/opt
      - sudo tar zxvf /media/debian/data/android.tgz -C /data/opt
   c. Change to /data/opt/android/avd
   d. In SeqStudio.ini, set path to /data/opt/android/avd/SeqStudio.avd

5. Install InstrumentServer
   a. Download InstrumentServer:
      https://github.com/youngmin-kim-tfs/gsd-debian-aosp-public/releases/download/android-sdk/instrumentserver-seqstudio-1.2.6.dev.5-ci.tar.gz
   b. Untar instrumentserver-seqstudio-1.2.6.dev.5-ci.tar.gz to /data/opt
   c. Open /data/opt/InstrumentServer/Config/system.ini
      - Change devicemask to DEV:sd[b-z]*
   d. Open /data/opt/InstrumentServer/Config/locations.ini
      - Change [experiments] path to /data/experiments
      - Change [usbdrive] path to /media/usb0
      - Change [android] path to /data/opt/android
   e. Open SCPIServer/scpiSession.py
      - Change to:
        key = hmac.new(secret, challenge.endoe('utf-8'), md5).hexdigest()
   f. Open /data/opt/InstrumentServer/Methods/android.scpi
      - Comment out: ===> NOTE: this needs to be done after emulator launched
        ### Hostname update
        ### Timezone update
   g. Launch IS:
      - sudo /bin/python3 /data/opt/InstrumentServer/instrument.py

6. Run 3200.jar
   a. Download 3200.jar:
      http://10.253.253.198/job/Monarch-DataCollection-AOSP/lastSuccessfulBuild/artifact/3200/build/libs/3200.jar
   b. Move 3200.jar to /data/opt/Monarch/

7. Prepare KB
   a. Download KB:
      http://10.253.253.198/job/Monarch-KB/lastSuccessfulBuild/artifact/Basecaller-KB%201.4.2.9_patch.tar.gz
   b. Untar kb.tar.gz to /data/opt/Monarch/KB/

8. Download DataCollection SW
   a. Download DataCollection SW from:
      http://10.253.253.198/job/Monarch-DataCollection-AOSP/
   b. Move apk to /data/opt/Monarch/

9. Run Monarch
    a. Open terminal and change to /data/opt/Monarch
    b. Open /data/opt/Monarch/launcher.sh
    c. Check and change APK file name, accordinlgy, in launcher.sh
    b. Run Monarch:
       - ./launcher.sh



